Vice President Mike Pence met with Speaker of the National Assembly, Chung Sye-kyun, in Seoul, Republic of Korea. They discussed the importance of the U.S.-ROK alliance in maintaining peace and security in the Asia-Pacific region. They also emphasized the need for coordination to address the North Korean threat and reaffirmed their commitment to deploying THAAD. Pence assured that U.S. support for South Korea will remain unchanged, regardless of the outcome of the upcoming presidential election.